Multiplying these inequalities together, we get: \[ (1 + 2a)(2 + 2b)(2a + b) \geq 2\sqrt{2a} \cdot 4\sqrt{b} \cdot 2\sqrt{2ab} = 16ab \cdot 2 = 32ab. \] Equality in the AM-GM inequality holds if and only if all the terms are equal. Therefore, we need: 1. \(1 = 2a\) 2. \(1 = b\) 3. \(2a = b\) Solving these equations: 1. From \(1 = 2a\), we get \(a = \frac{1}{2}\). 2. From \(1 = b\), we get \(b = 1\). 3.
